14
[h4 id=WhoIsQuietust 
	" Who is "Quietust"?
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"He's a human male who, among other things, is interested in the way the 8-bit Nintendo Entertainment System works.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=WhatSortOfStuffHasHeDone 
	" What sort of stuff has he done?
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"All sorts of stuff.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Long ago, he released the 7th version of a mIRC script called "ircN".
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Later, he and a friend took a poorly coded web-based strategy game, rewrote it completely, and released it as "QM Promisance". Years later, once he actually knew how to code in PHP "properly", he rewrote it from scratch yet again, making it more extensible and also resistant to attack.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Somewhere along the line, he took the remains of a half-written NES emulator (called NinthStar), rewrote it completely, and released 
	[a href=https://www.qmtpro.com/~nes/nintendulator/ rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Nintendulator
	]a
	". It is still under development, but updates are very infrequent (and actual releases tend to be many years apart).
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"Later, he traced high-resolution photographs of the NTSC NES CPU and PPU, converted them into netlists, then combined it with code from the 
	[a href=http://visual6502.org/ rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Visual6502
	]a
	" project in order to create the 
	[a href=https://www.qmtpro.com/~nes/chipimages/visual2a03/ rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Visual 2A03
	]a
	" and 
	[a href=https://www.qmtpro.com/~nes/chipimages/visual2c02/ rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Visual 2C02
	]a
	".
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"He's also make significant contributions to "DFHack", a memory modification library written for the game 
	[a href=http://www.bay12games.com/dwarves/ rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Dwarf Fortress
	]a
	", both by reverse-engineering the game's data structures and writing plugins to do special things with them.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
]div
